                                                </gloss>
                                        </item>
                                        <item>
                                                <gloss type="term" xml:id="UT22084-089-006-47">
                                                        <term>five misdeeds with immediate retribution</term>
                                                        <term xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" status="verified">mtshams med pa lnga </term>
                                                        <term xml:lang="bo">མཚམས་མེད་པ་ལྔ།</term>
                                                        <term xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" status="verified">pañcānantarya</term>
                                                        <term type="definition">The five most negative actions. Upon death, those who have committed
                                                                one or more of these immediately proceed to the hells without first experiencing the
                                                                intermediate state. They are (1) killing an arhat, (2) killing one’s mother, (3)
                                                                killing one’s father, (4) creating a schism in the saṅgha, and (5) maliciously drawing
                                                                blood from a tathāgata’s body.</term>
                                                </gloss>
                                        </item>
